    "6841125": {
      "title": "Continuous requirement for the TCR in regulatory T cell function",
      "abstract": "Regulatory T cells help to keep adaptive immunity in check. Rudensky and colleagues show that these cells continuously require TCR signaling to maintain their cellular identity and homeostasis and to exert their suppressive ability."
